Manufactured in the U.S.A Anybody can solve ordinary waste water pumping problems. At See Water Inc., we've built our reputation on our unique ability to solve difficult problems on a daily basis. Our patented spill prevention technology has been protecting the environment since 1995. We design and manufacture innovative electrical pump controls, high liquid alarms and pump control panels for commercial, industrial and utility companies. Manufactured in the U.S.A., our products are backed with 3-year warranties, 24-hour troubleshooting, personalized customer service and competitive pricing. One of the biggest challenges in pumping water from oil containment areas, elevator sumps and underground utility vaults is how to pump water into waterways while containing the oil. Our Oil Smart:registered: System incorporates pump controls and alarm sensors that differentiate between oil and water, allowing companies to responsibly discharge the water without worrying about contamination. This not only keeps companies in compliance with local, state and federal regulations, it helps build their reputation as “green” businesses that protect the environment. Located in San Jacinto, Calif., See Water Inc. was founded in 1995 with the primary focus of creating quality custom and pre-engineered control panels for waste water, dewatering and oil containment applications. Our patented technology and innovative products have been hailed by industry leaders and environmentalists alike for protecting our environment. See Water Inc. products are sold through a worldwide network of manufacturing representatives and distributors.

Description: Human Factor Analytics delivers a risk analytics tool and data warehouse for small to mid-size self-insured employers, healthcare.
Full Description: Human Factor Analytics delivers a risk analytics tool and data warehouse for small to mid-size self-insured employers, healthcare benefits brokers, and wellness providers to analyze risk and identify what is driving present and future cost. HFA takes disparate data sets – healthcare utilization data, biometric data, pharmacy data, health risk appraisal data, and workers comp data – and integrates the data into a relational database. We are currently adapting our system to take in absenteeism and productivity data and injury data. HFA can then query the data and discover relationships in order to determine what drives disease risk and cost to the employer. From the analysis, HFA suggests solutions to mitigate risk and reduce cost. HFA answers the question asked by employers and benefits managers who find themselves unable to effectively cope with the current healthcare crisis. All suggested risk mitigation solutions can be pre/post tested through a statistical application within the Human Factor platform. Our software is friendly to the end-user and affordable for our target market. We anticipate a substantial, persistent interest in our company and our software.
Industry Groups: Administrative Services, Health Care, Information Technology

Description: Pyrocool Technologies develops and distributes fire extinguishment and cooling products.
Full Description: Pyrocool Technologies wanted to develop products which avoided the side effects of global environmental damage and long term potential toxicity to humans found in conventional firefighting chemicals. They decided to take an approach different from the fifty year old concept of “film-sealing” a fire through the use of fluorocarbons and glycol ethers. Unlike conventional products, Pyrocool agents were developed to attack the heat component of the traditional fire triangle. By cooling fire site temperatures, Pyrocool products deprive fire of one of its essential element while at the same time increasing firefighting access and decreasing extinguishment time. Their products include pyrocool FEF and pyrocool aerosol.
